          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Hieroglyphs (from Greek: \"sacred writing\") are Egypt's pictographic writing system developed around 3200 BC. They consist of over 700 signs representing sounds, words, or concepts.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">For centuries, hieroglyphs remained an unsolved mystery — until the discovery of the <strong>Rosetta Stone</strong> in 1799. This stone contains the same text in three scripts: hieroglyphic, demotic, and ancient Greek.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Thomas Young and Jean-François Champollion successfully deciphered hieroglyphs in 1822, reopening the window to rich ancient Egyptian civilization.</p>",
